LET::::- \"The Remarkable Fidgety River\" (1979)\nITV\n\"Not the Nine O'Clock News\"\nBULLET::::- Unknown episodes (1979)\nBBC Two\n\"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\"\nBULLET::::- 6 episodes (1981)\nBBC Two\n\"Hyperland\"\nBULLET::::- Television documentary (1990)\nBBC Two\n\"Doctor Who: The Lost Episode\"\nBULLET::::- Television special (2018) (1980’s unaired \"Shada\", with animated inserts of sections not completed in 1980)\nBBC America\n\nBULLET::::- Adams, Douglas (1998). Is there an Artificial God?, speech at \"Digital Biota 2\", Cambridge, England, September 1998.\nBULLET::::- Dawkins, Richard (2003). \"Eulogy for Douglas Adams,\" in \"A devil's chaplain: reflections on hope, lies, science, and love\". Houghton Mifflin Harcourt.\nBULLET::::- Felch, Laura (2004). Don't Panic: Douglas Adams and the Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy by Neil Gaiman, May 2004\nBULLET::::- Ray, Mohit K (2007). \"Atlantic Companion to Literature in English\", Atlantic Publishers and Distributors.\nBULLET::::- Webb, Nick (2005a). \"Wish You Were Here: The Official Biography of Douglas Adams\". Ballantine Books.\nBULLET::::- Webb, Nick (2005b). \"Adams, Douglas Noël (1952–2001)\", \"Oxford Dictionary of National Biography\", Oxford University Press, January 2005. Retrieved 25 October 2005.\nBULLET::::- Roberts, Jem (2014) \"The Frood: The Authorised & Very Official Biography of Douglas Adams & The Hitchhiker's Guide To The Galaxy\" Preface Publishing. \"The Frood\"\n\nBULLET::::- Herbert, R. (1980). The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (Book Review). Library Journal, 105(16), 1982.\nBULLET::::- Adams, J., & Brown, R. (1981). The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (Book Review). School Library Journal, 27(5), 74.\nBULLET::::- Nickerson, S. L. (1982). The Restaurant at the End of the Universe (Book). Library Journal, 107(4), 476.\nBULLET::::- Nickerson, S. L. (1982). Life, the Universe, and Everything (Book). Library Journal, 107(18), 2007.\nBULLET::::- Morner, C. (1982). The Restaur