eing in 1980.\nBULLET::::- Republic of Texas: the Texas dollar was issued between January 1839 and September 1840.\nBULLET::::- Zimbabwe: once used the Zimbabwe dollar, but abolished it and now uses the South African rand, the US dollar, the Euro, the Pound sterling, the Botswana pula, the Chinese yuan, the Indian rupee and the Japanese yen.\n\nBULLET::::- Canadian Tire money\nBULLET::::- Disney dollars\nBULLET::::- Eurodollar\nBULLET::::- Fiat money\nBULLET::::- List of circulating currencies\nBULLET::::- North American currency union Amero\nBULLET::::- Petrodollar\nBULLET::::- United States one hundred-dollar bill\nBULLET::::- Dollar, Clackmannanshire, a town in Scotland\n\nBULLET::::- Etymonline (word history). for \"buck\"; Etymonline (word history) for \"dollar\"\nBULLET::::- Currency converter. CNNMoney.com\n"}
